5|$|Highly {{energetic}} {{chemistry is}} thought to have produced a self-replicating molecule around 4 <b>billion</b> <b>years</b> ago, and half a <b>billion</b> <b>years</b> later the last common ancestor of all life existed. The current scientific consensus is that the complex biochemistry that makes up life came from simpler chemical reactions. The beginning of life may have included self-replicating molecules such as RNA and the assembly of simple cells.|$|E
