50|$|At the Paris Conference in 2015 {{where the}} Agreement was negotiated, the {{developed}} countries reaffirmed the commitment to mobilize $100 <b>billion</b> a <b>year</b> in climate finance by 2020, and agreed to continue mobilizing finance {{at the level of}} $100 <b>billion</b> a <b>year</b> until 2025. The commitment refers to the pre-existing plan to provide US$100 <b>billion</b> a <b>year</b> in aid to developing countries for actions on climate change adaptation and mitigation.|$|R
